Using the search-instagram-creators tool, find creators posting in this niche. Then use instagram-profile to vet the top candidates. Return a JSON array of the 5 best fits with: handle, recipientId, followerCount, engagementSignal, reason.

Brand profile:
- Name: {{$.steps.brand-research.title}}
- Tone: {{$.steps.brand-research.tone}}
- Values: {{$.steps.brand-research.values}}
- Products: {{$.steps.brand-research.products}}

Creators to contact:
{{$.steps.find-creators.text}}

For each creator in the list, call send-instagram-dm with a personalised message. The message should:
1. Reference the brand by name
2. Mention something specific about why this creator fits
3. Propose a collaboration (gifting, paid partnership, or UGC brief)
4. Keep it under 200 characters — DM length limit
5. Match the brand tone perfectly

Scrape this trend/editorial URL and extract fashion trend signals:

URL: {{$.input.trendUrl}}

Use the scrape-url tool then structure your findings as JSON with: trends, colours, culturalRefs, keywords, summary.

Write marketing copy for {{$.input.productName}} ({{$.input.productCategory}}).

Brand profile:
- Name: {{$.steps.brand-research.title}}
- Description: {{$.steps.brand-research.description}}
- Tone: {{$.steps.brand-research.tone}}
- Target audience: {{$.steps.brand-research.targetAudience}}
- Values: {{$.steps.brand-research.values}}

Trend context (from {{$.input.trendUrl}}):
{{$.steps.scrape-trends.text}}

Deliver:
1. PRODUCT DESCRIPTION (150-200 words) — for the PDP. Match the brand voice exactly.
2. INSTAGRAM CAPTION (under 150 chars + 5 hashtags) — punchy, brand-appropriate, scroll-stopping.
3. EMAIL SUBJECT LINE (under 50 chars) — for a launch email. A/B test: give 2 options.
4. REASONING (2-3 sentences) — why these copy choices fit this specific brand and trend moment.

No hedging. Write like you'd stake your agency's reputation on it.
